[resource]
script = ExtResource("1_uscna")
reagent_id = "NH3"
title = "Ammonia"
body = "[b]Basic facts[/b]
[table=2]
[cell]Formula:[/cell][cell]NH₃[/cell]
[cell]Molar mass:[/cell][cell]17 g/mol[/cell]
[cell]State at room temperature:[/cell][cell]Gas[/cell]
[cell]Color:[/cell][cell]Colorless[/cell]
[cell]Smell:[/cell][cell]Sharp, strong odor[/cell]
[/table]
[b]Formation reaction[/b]
N₂ + 3H₂ → 2NH₃
[b]Important properties[/b]
• Basic gas that dissolves easily in water.
• Forms ammonium hydroxide (NH₄OH) in solution.
• Lighter than air.
• Can react with acids to form ammonium salts.
[b]Where ammonia is found[/b]
• Produced by decomposition of organic matter.
• Found in small amounts in the atmosphere.
• Produced industrially from nitrogen and hydrogen.
[b]Uses[/b]
• Production of fertilizers.
• Used in cleaning products.
• Important chemical in industry.
[b]Safety[/b]
Toxic and irritating gas that can damage the eyes and lungs in high concentrations."
